[thinking] **Considering JVM agent challenges**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about the dynamic-access agent and its relation to the JVM. The command line likely includes `javaagent` in the system properties, but it might not automatically get passed to child processes. I wonder if using `ProcessBuilder` could inherit `JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS` with the agent, but I’m not sure. This situation isn’t ideal; it could violate certain conditions under native environments. Plus, launching Java from Native Image might not support dynamic JVM spawning, which raises more questions.
